abstract: Here are five things that happened on the campaign trail that you may have missed.
snippet: Here are five things that happened on the campaign trail that you may have missed.
lead_paragraph: Congratulations on surviving another week in American politics. We would reassure you that next week will be calmer, but we’re not allowed to lie.

abstract: Centrist Democrats portrayed Boris Johnson’s victory as a warning sign for the American election. Progressives said there were few similarities between the two political races.
snippet: Centrist Democrats portrayed Boris Johnson’s victory as a warning sign for the American election. Progressives said there were few similarities between the two political races.
lead_paragraph: Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. conjured the prospect of headlines like, “Look what happens when the Labour Party moves so, so far to the left.” Former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg said that “Jeremy Corbyn’s catastrophic showing in the U.K. is a clear warning.” And Mayor Pete Buttigieg spoke of the need to “build a coalition and gather that majority.”

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg broadly, repeatedly — and wrongly — took a huge amount of credit Friday for driving the U.S. coal industry to its knees.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg broadly, repeatedly — and wrongly — took a huge amount of credit Friday for driving the U.S. coal industry to its knees.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg broadly, repeatedly — and wrongly — took a huge amount of credit Friday for driving the U.S. coal industry to its knees.
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Bloomberg Says He's Killing Coal. He's Not
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Bloomberg Says He's Killing Coal. He's Not

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday unveiled a climate plan to slash U.S. carbon emissions by 50% in ten years, by slapping tougher pollution standards on new gas-fired power plants and replacing coal with cleaner energy sources like wind and solar.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday unveiled a climate plan to slash U.S. carbon emissions by 50% in ten years, by slapping tougher pollution standards on new gas-fired power plants and replacing coal with cleaner energy ...
lead_paragraph: ALEXANDRIA, Va. — Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday unveiled a climate plan to slash U.S. carbon emissions by 50% in ten years, by slapping tougher pollution standards on new gas-fired power plants and replacing coal with cleaner energy sources like wind and solar.
headline_main: Bloomberg Climate Plan Would Halve U.S. Carbon Emissions in 10 Years
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Climate Plan Would Halve U.S. Carbon Emissions in 10 Years

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday unveiled a broad plan to eliminate all coal power plants and slow the expansion of the natural gas sector as part of a policy to fight climate change that he says would cut carbon emissions across the U.S. economy by 50% over the first 10 years.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday unveiled a broad plan to eliminate all coal power plants and slow the expansion of the natural gas sector as part of a policy to fight climate change that he says would cut carbon emiss...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg on Friday unveiled a broad plan to eliminate all coal power plants and slow the expansion of the natural gas sector as part of a policy to fight climate change that he says would cut carbon emissions across the U.S. economy by 50% over the first 10 years.
headline_main: Bloomberg Plan to Reduce Carbon Emissions by 50% in 10 Years
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Plan to Reduce Carbon Emissions by 50% in 10 Years

abstract: ‘Trump anxiety disorder’ has morphed into anxiety about everything, and impeachment isn’t helping.
snippet: ‘Trump anxiety disorder’ has morphed into anxiety about everything, and impeachment isn’t helping.
lead_paragraph: GREENWOOD, S.C. — The past three years have not been easy for the political fortunes or the emotional health of America’s Democrats. To the extent they feel optimistic about anything, they have been waiting for the 2020 election in the way inhabitants of a storm-ravaged city might look toward the end of hurricane season — as an opportunity to restore order not just to their fractured physical world, but to their battered psyches.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's doctor has proclaimed him "a 77-year-old man in outstanding health," according to a letter released by his campaign on Thursday.

lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's doctor has proclaimed him "a 77-year-old man in outstanding health," according to a letter released by his campaign on Thursday.
headline_main: Democratic Presidential Candidate Bloomberg in 'Outstanding Health': Doctor

abstract: Michael Bloomberg is in “outstanding health,” but a letter from his doctor released Thursday notes that the 77-year-old Democratic presidential candidate is receiving treatment for several medical conditions, including an irregular heartbeat.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg is in “outstanding health,” but a letter from his doctor released Thursday notes that the 77-year-old Democratic presidential candidate is receiving treatment for several medical conditions, including an irregular heartbeat.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Bloomberg is in “outstanding health,” but a letter from his doctor released Thursday notes that the 77-year-old Democratic presidential candidate is receiving treatment for several medical conditions, including an irregular heartbeat.
headline_main: Doctor: Democrat Bloomberg, 77, Is in 'Outstanding Health'
headline_print_headline: Doctor: Democrat Bloomberg, 77, Is in 'Outstanding Health'

abstract: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
snippet: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
headline_main: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate

abstract: Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remains in doubt past March.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remain...
lead_paragraph: HARRISBURG, Pa. — Elizabeth Warren's campaign is moving to become the first in the Democratic presidential primary to hire field staff and open field offices in Pennsylvania, early moves in a late primary state that could be an important prize if the nominee remains in doubt past March.
headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Gets Campaign Effort Going in Pennsylvania
headline_print_headline: Elizabeth Warren Gets Campaign Effort Going in Pennsylvania
